August Calvin Smith ❤️ 8.26.23

He’s here! So completely overwhelmed with joy. We thought that we were done building our little family. After my ectopic pregnancy last year and then losing my Mom after, our hearts changed. A few weeks before she passed, she looked at me with joy filled eyes and said “and we’re gonna have a baby soon!” She had no idea that just before, David and I had talked about how we felt like we wanted to try for a boy to complete our little family. Feels like he was gifted to us straight from her ❤️

PS. We had the name picked out before even becoming pregnant! Had no idea he’d come in August. Calvin is a family name from David’s side. Also felt fitting that Mom’s favorite season was summer 🥹

Our newest addition! #ElkayPartner We love our new ezH2O Liv filtered water dispenser from @elkay_usa ! It gives us easier access to fresh, cold, filtered water without contaminants. Basement reno before and after 👀 #diy #diyhomeprojects

The longest and most cruel journey ended one year ago today. I still find myself fighting with thoughts like “she should still be here” and “she didn’t deserve that”. It’s been a hard year of grief and sadness without her infectious smile and I think I’ll always fear I may forget her voice. But I find comfort in knowing she’s no longer suffering, and thinking about how, just maybe, she hand picked our sweet little boy and delivered him straight to us to help us heal ❤️ I love you, Mom. #earlyonsetalzheimers #alz #alzheimers
